SN  - 0022-1082
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1540-6261.1991.tb04648.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - ABSTRACT Lookback options are path dependent contingent claims whose payoffs depend on the extrema of a given security's price over a certain period of time. Using probabilistic tools, we derive explicit formulas for various European lookback options, and provide some results about their American counterparts.
ER  - 

TY  - JOUR
T1  - New Evidence on The January Effect Before Personal Income Taxes
AU  - JONES, STEVEN L.
AU  - LEE, WINSON
AU  - APENBRINK, RUDOLF
Y1  - 1991/12/01
PY  - 1991
DA  - 1991/12/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1540-6261.1991.tb04649.x
T2  - The Journal of Finance
JF  - The Journal of Finance
JO  - The Journal of Finance
JA  - The Journal of Finance
SP  - 1909
EP  - 1924
VL  - 46
IS  - 5
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0022-1082
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1540-6261.1991.tb04649.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - ABSTRACT We examine the returns of stocks in Cowles Industrial Index before and after the introduction of personal income taxes in 1917. This is distinct from earlier studies because we cross-sectionally analyze the relationship between the returns of the individual stocks and measures of tax-loss selling potential and size. We find that excess returns at the turn-of-the-year and for the month of January were not significant until after 1917. These results provide strong support for the tax-loss selling hypothesis as an explanation for the January seasonal in the returns of small firms.
ER  - 

TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Valuation Effects of Private Placements of Convertible Debt
AU  - FIELDS, L. PAIGE
AU  - MAIS, ERIC L.
